This is a shell script for backing up BITNAMI redmine application
Only database file and uploaded files are backed up.

To use this script please follow below steps:
1. Open daily_backup script, check below variables:
   REDMINE_DIR, BACKUP_DIR, BACKUP_TMP_DIR.
   modify them if neccessary.
2. run daily_backup once, check if backup is success;
3. if step succeeds, go to terminal and run below command:
    sudo crontab -e
   an editor will pop up, add folowing command at the end of editor:
   0 0 * * * cd /home/CORPUSERS/28850586/Downloads/redmine/bin && ./backup_run/daily_backup






Reference:
How to backup and update the BitNami Redmine Stack
http://bitnami.org/article/how-to-backup-and-update-the-bitnami-redmine-stack
http://www.redmine.org/projects/redmine/wiki/HowTo_Migrate_Redmine_to_a_new_server_to_a_new_Redmine_version
HowTo keep in sync your git repository for redmine
http://www.redmine.org/projects/redmine/wiki/HowTo_keep_in_sync_your_git_repository_for_redmine
